From: nix-wasm <eric@codebutler.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] wasm: !MMU read-only MAP_SHARED file mmap falls back to a private copy

On !MMU a MAP_SHARED file mapping needs a directly-addressable backing
(NOMMU_MAP_DIRECT, i.e. the file provides ->get_unmapped_area) or
validate_mmap_request() rejects it with -ENODEV. Filesystems that can only
be copied into memory (9p — including the served Nix store — romfs, ...)
report NOMMU_MAP_COPY only, so even a read-only MAP_SHARED mmap of a file on
them fails.

But a read-only shared mapping has nothing to share-write: it is
semantically identical to MAP_PRIVATE. Downgrade such mappings to
MAP_PRIVATE when the backing cannot be mapped directly, so they are
satisfied by a private copy of the file (do_mmap_private) instead of
failing. This makes read-only mmap() of files work as on a normal system —
needed by libxkbcommon, which mmap()s the XKB rules files with
(PROT_READ, MAP_SHARED) and whose failure aborted GTK keymap creation
("Couldn't read rules file ...: No such device" -> "Failed to create XKB
keymap"); SQLite's mmap, fontconfig, etc. benefit equally. Mirrors how
anonymous MAP_SHARED is mapped to MAP_PRIVATE on !MMU (there is no fork()).

Shared writable mappings (PROT_WRITE) and directly-mappable backings
(e.g. chardevs with ->get_unmapped_area) are unaffected.
---
--- a/mm/nommu.c
+++ b/mm/nommu.c
@@ -1028,6 +1028,20 @@
 
 	*populate = 0;
 
+	/*
+	 * !MMU: a read-only MAP_SHARED file mapping has nothing to share-write,
+	 * so it is semantically identical to MAP_PRIVATE. When the backing cannot
+	 * be mapped directly (no ->get_unmapped_area, e.g. 9p / the served Nix
+	 * store), satisfy it with a private copy of the file instead of failing
+	 * validate_mmap_request() with -ENODEV. This makes read-only mmap() of
+	 * files work as on a normal system (libxkbcommon XKB rules, SQLite mmap,
+	 * fontconfig, ...). Mirrors how anonymous MAP_SHARED is mapped to
+	 * MAP_PRIVATE on !MMU (there is no fork()).
+	 */
+	if (file && (flags & MAP_TYPE) == MAP_SHARED && !(prot & PROT_WRITE) &&
+	    !file->f_op->get_unmapped_area)
+		flags = (flags & ~MAP_TYPE) | MAP_PRIVATE;
+
 	/* decide whether we should attempt the mapping, and if so what sort of
 	 * mapping */
 	ret = validate_mmap_request(file, addr, len, prot, flags, pgoff,
